Implemented the fix in place.

Changed:
- `clap_builder/src/parser/arg_matcher.rs`
  - Added `Clone` to `ArgMatcher`.

- `clap_builder/src/parser/parser.rs`
  - Updated `Parser::did_you_mean_error` so the suggested argument is added only to a cloned matcher for usage rendering.
  - This prevents the real parse matcher from being polluted when `ignore_errors(true)` suppresses the error, allowing defaults to be applied correctly.

Verified with:

```bash
cargo test -p clap --test builder ignore_errors
cargo test -p clap --test builder did_you_mean --features suggestions,error-context
cargo fmt --check
```

All passed.
